<item>
            <title>[DATAMONGO-891] Custom enum value serialization</title>
                <link>https://jira.spring.io/browse/DATAMONGO-891</link>
                <project id="10701" key="DATAMONGO">Spring Data MongoDB</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;I have some enums whose Java names are fairly long and detailed; they each have a short value for use in file names, JSON responses, and so on. Jackson provides framework support for substituting an alternate serialization value simply by annotating an enum field with &lt;tt&gt;@JsonValue&lt;/tt&gt; (providing, of course, that the field values are unique across all the enum values). It would be useful to have such support available with a common mapper for all enum types.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;(This might be suitable for Commons, but I&apos;m not sure whether putting it there would conflict with store-specific approaches like JPA &lt;tt&gt;EnumType&lt;/tt&gt;.)&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
